    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect FFT results due to cmac() function bug in ARM NEON implementation\n\n### Summary\nThe cmac() function in the ARM NEON optimized FFT implementation had incorrect ordering of operations for creating conjugate and flipped versions of input vectors. This caused incorrect FFT computations in 5G NR signal processing.\n\nThe issue manifests as incorrect channel estimation and beamforming weights, leading to degraded downlink performance on ARM-based platforms.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Fixed cmac() function to create conjugate before flipping for proper FFT calculations.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Run NR gNB on ARM-based platform (aarch64)\n2. Configure with 100MHz bandwidth and 64 antenna elements\n3. Observe degraded PDSCH BLER (>10%) compared to x86 reference\n4. Channel estimates show incorrect phase rotation\n\nThe fix ensures cmac() produces mathematically correct results matching the x86 implementation.\n"
}